%F A001809 If we define f(n,i,x) = Sum_{k=i..n} (Sum_{j=i..k}(C(k,j)*Stirling1(n,k)*Stirling2(j,i)*x^(k-j))) then a(n)=(-1)^n*f(n,2,-3), (n>=2). - _Milan Janjic_, Mar 01 2009
